## What works on remote hosts without installing anything

| Capability | Works on remote without install? | Why |
|---|---|---|
| bash tab completion (paths, files) | Yes | bash + bash-completion already on most Linux servers |
| bash tab completion (git, docker, etc.) | Partial — depends on server | Needs bash-completion pkg AND tool-specific scripts on the server |
| ctrl-r history search | Yes | Built into bash everywhere |
| Visual/fuzzy history (fzf, atuin) | No | Must be installed on remote |
| Starship prompt | No | Must be installed on remote |
| Fish autosuggestions | No | Fish must be installed on remote |

### What a plain `ssh host` gives you for free

- Tab completion for files and paths: yes
- Tab completion for git branches, docker, etc.: yes if the server has those packages
- ctrl-r reverse search: yes, but it is a plain text search, not visual
- Nice prompt: no — you get whatever the server's default bash prompt is
- Syntax highlighting: no

