## SSH to remote hosts

ControlMaster is configured globally in `~/.ssh/config` under `Host *` so all
SSH connections automatically reuse an existing socket. No wrapper needed.

```bash
ssh fastpi     # plain ssh, ControlMaster applies automatically
```

### Changes made to `~/.ssh/config`

Added to the `Host *` block:

```
ControlMaster auto
ControlPath ~/.ssh/cm/%r@%h:%p
ControlPersist 10m
ServerAliveInterval 30
ServerAliveCountMax 3
```

### Local files created

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `~/.ssh/cm/` | ControlMaster socket directory |
| `~/.config/fish/functions/sshr.fish` | Simple SSH wrapper (just passes args through) |
| `~/.config/starship.toml` | Starship config |

---

## Reverting everything

### Remove from a remote host (if you ever manually installed anything)

```bash
ssh <host> 'rm -f ~/.local/bin/starship ~/.local/bin/atuin ~/.config/starship.toml ~/.config/fish/config.fish'
# If fish was installed via apt:
ssh <host> 'sudo apt-get remove -y fish'
```

### Remove local files

```bash
rm ~/.config/fish/functions/sshr.fish
rm ~/.config/starship.toml   # only if you did not have one before

# ControlMaster sockets — list then kill, then remove directory
ls ~/.ssh/cm/
ssh -O exit git@github.com   # repeat for each entry listed
rm -f ~/.ssh/cm/*
rmdir ~/.ssh/cm
```

### Revert `~/.ssh/config`

Remove these five lines from the `Host *` block:

```
ControlMaster auto
ControlPath ~/.ssh/cm/%r@%h:%p
ControlPersist 10m
ServerAliveInterval 30
ServerAliveCountMax 3
```
